12: ## Theme Settings Bug Fix
13: *   **The Issue**: Our glassmorphic modifiers (`Modifier.appleGlass()` and `Modifier.appleGlassRow()`) and card colors (`appleCardColors()`, `appleSurfaceColor()`, etc.) checked `isSystemInDarkTheme()` to decide which colors (light/dark) to apply. However, since the app allows users to explicitly toggle Light/Dark Mode via settings (independent of the Android system setting), this system check caused components to remain stuck in dark mode if the user's Android OS was set to dark theme.
14: *   **The Solution**: Replaced all instances of `isSystemInDarkTheme()` in [AppleComponents.kt](file:///c:/Users/mayan/Desktop/musicapp/Echo-Music/app/src/main/kotlin/com/music/echo/ui/component/AppleComponents.kt), [Items.kt](file:///c:/Users/mayan/Desktop/musicapp/Echo-Music/app/src/main/kotlin/com/music/echo/ui/component/Items.kt), [NavigationTitle.kt](file:///c:/Users/mayan/Desktop/musicapp/Echo-Music/app/src/main/kotlin/com/music/echo/ui/component/NavigationTitle.kt), and [HomeScreen.kt](file:///c:/Users/mayan/Desktop/musicapp/Echo-Music/app/src/main/kotlin/com/music/echo/ui/screens/HomeScreen.kt) with a dynamic check based on the active theme background color:
15:     ```kotlin
16:     val colorScheme = MaterialTheme.colorScheme
17:     val isDark = (colorScheme.background.red + colorScheme.background.green + colorScheme.background.blue) < 1.5f
18:     ```
19:     This dynamically and accurately resolves the theme state matching the user's active setting choice.
20: 
